    {
        "content": "<p>Presumably, the actual definition of <code>IsAbsolutelyIrreducible</code> can remain more concrete, but there should be API saying that every <code>IsBaseChange</code> is irreducible.</p>",
        "id": 568313233,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Browning",
        "timestamp": 1768511842
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, is it sufficient to ask for irreducibility over the algebraic closure? Because that would avoid the quantification over types.</p>",
        "id": 568313306,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Browning",
        "timestamp": 1768511891
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"253861\">Thomas Browning</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/416277-FLT/topic/Definition.20of.20absolute.20irreducibility/near/568313306\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also, is it sufficient to ask for irreducibility over the algebraic closure? Because that would avoid the quantification over types.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It is equivalent to just irreducibility over the algebraic closure, and I’m trying to prove that as a theorem. I also replaced locally in my file Field with Field.{u}, so that it’s quantifying over the fields in the same universe as k only.</p>",
        "id": 568316246,
